  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Data Platform Engineer（Architect）",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead MySQL / Aurora schema governance, including standards for table design, column definitions, naming, indexing, and documentation.</li><li>Collaborate closely with Data BPs, Data Engineers, and Application Developers to drive data governance from source systems and improve upstream data quality.</li><li>Operate the DDL / Schema Review workflow to ensure all schema changes align with standards and support downstream data platform requirements.</li><li>Identify and remediate common structural issues (e.g., improper data types, inconsistent naming, schema mismatches between test and production).</li><li>Provide guidance to application developers and assist in SQL analysis and optimization to resolve common performance issues in business queries.</li><li>Promote schema and environment consistency across test and production systems.</li><li>Support security, compliance, and audit needs (access control, privilege management, sensitive data identification).</li><li>No infrastructure-level DBA duties (no deployment, HA operations, or backup management).</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>5 years relevant working experience</li><li>Strong understanding of relational schema design, data types, indexing strategy, and data modeling principles.</li><li>Ability to analyze and optimize business SQL queries using tools like EXPLAIN / execution plans, indexing strategies, etc.</li><li>Experience working with data teams (Data BPs / Data Engineers) and application developers on data quality and governance initiatives.</li><li>Familiar with Linux/Unix fundamentals.</li><li>Experience in data governance or data platform projects is a plus.</li><li>Financial or transactional system experience preferred.</li><li>Able to use chinese and english as daily working language to align with chinses speaking stakeholders</li></ul>",
